<br>
- Monster Summoning line improved to where it's taken seriously as a part of our arsenal. If this line was intended as a joke, it should have began and ended with Monster Summoning I. Preferablly the pet summoned with this spell would be unique from our other pets, not just an elemental hiding in another model.<br>
<br>
- Burnout IV given a 5% haste boost. This would put it square between Burnout III and Burnout V, I think that's fair. The spell as is, even with the haste cap fixed, is hardly an upgrade at all.<br>
<br>
- Pet heals are only worth using with the epic pet currently. They're far too inefficient to use on normal pets over chain casting. I'd like that looked at somehow.<br>
<br>
- Fix Frenzied Burnout to be the uber AA skill is should have been from day one.<br>
<br>
- Make pet's spells a proc, or fix the issue with casting screwing up the melee timer.<br>
<br>
- Make something that allows pets to hit bane only mobs. Not much of an issue to me, but I know for pet classes who raid such mobs, it must be frustrating in the extreme.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
